Cybersecurity Consultant Report
Objective

This report provides recommendations to improve the cybersecurity posture of the college.

Top Five Risks
Data Breach
Malware Infection
Phishing Attacks
Weak Passwords
Insider Threats
Top Five Recommendations
Enable Multi-Factor Authentication
Conduct Regular Security Training
Maintain Regular Backups
Keep Systems Updated
Implement Strong Access Controls
Expected Benefits
Improved data security
Reduced cyber risks
Better compliance
Increased system availability
Enhanced trust among students and staff
Conclusion

Implementing these cybersecurity measures will strengthen the college's security posture, reduce potential risks, and protect valuable information assets.